<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 08 at 4:13PM CST  by NWS Jackson</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT CENTRAL RANKIN...CENTRAL HINDS
AND MADISON COUNTIES THROUGH 500 PM CST...
At 413 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clinton, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Jackson, Madison, Ridgeland, Flowood, and Pocahontas around 420 PM
CST.
Canton, Gluckstadt, and Annandale around 425 PM CST.
Sharon around 440 PM CST.
Farmhaven and Way around 445 PM CST.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
